content:
The Vlocity Cards Framework supports versioning for all components. The name, author, and version combination must be unique for each component of a given type (layout, card, or template) in an org.

Use the following fields to create unique versions of a component:

Name - Components are requested by name.
Author - Specifies the user organization that created the record.
Version - An integer that increases by one with every new version.

Only one active record per name is allowed in an org. Activating a component deactivates all other components of the same type that have the same name.

Multiple versions of a component can exist, but only one version at a time can be active.

Creating a version of a component creates an exact copy of the record with a Version equal to the latest version number plus one.

When deploying components in a new org, you must export any applicable Vlocity Cards framework components, particularly those that you modified. Only active versions are exported.

Follow Vlocity's requirements and best practices when naming cards and card layouts. Consider the following best practices for versioning in OmniStudio:
